# Cron (vtigercron)

## Flow

1. `cron/vtigercron.php` → `App\Modules\Cron\Bootstrap::init()` (ROOT_DIRECTORY, config, Yii).
2. `App\Modules\Cron\Runner\CronRunner::run($serviceName)` — without `service=`, runs all active tasks.
3. Task registry: `vtiger_cron_task` (`name` = `LBL_*`, `handler_class`, `frequency` in seconds, `status`).
4. Handler: `handler_class` must implement `App\Modules\Cron\Contract\CronTaskInterface` (often `AbstractCronTask` or `src/Modules/*/Cron/*Task.php`).
5. `CronRunner::runTask()`: checks frequency / stuck `status=2` → `markRunning()` → `execute()` → `markFinished()` (even after an exception).

## Running and logs

- Docker (every minute): `cron` service → `php cron/vtigercron.php`.
- Single task: `docker compose exec -T app php cron/vtigercron.php service=LBL_WORKFLOW`
- Output: `cache/logs/cron.log` (stdout). Errors: `cache/logs/system.log` — search `[CRON]`.
- `service=…` skips frequency (immediate run).

## `vtiger_cron_task.status`

- `0` disabled, `1` enabled, `2` running (may stick after a crash — unlock with `UPDATE … SET status=1`).

## Rules when changing cron code

- **Do not use** `App\Db\Db::pquery()` — use `\App\Db\Query` / `createCommand()` (legacy: `PearDatabase::getInstance()`).
- **Not** `(new \yii\db\Query())` — cron bootstrap has no `Yii::$app->db`; `\App\Db\Query` resolves via `Db::getInstance()`.
- CLI has no HTTP session — runner sets admin via `Users\Models\Record::setCurrentUserId()`; do not use `$request`.
- Exceptions are caught and logged; the task still gets `markFinished()` — one failure does not stop the whole cron run.
- CardDAV/CalDAV: `config/api.php` (`$enableCardDAV`, `$enableCalDAV`) — DAV cron should early-return when disabled.
- New task: row in `vtiger_cron_task` + handler class; patterns: `src/Modules/Cron/Tasks/*.php` or `src/Modules/<Module>/Cron/*Task.php`.

## Mail queue (`MailerTask`)

- Handler: `src/Modules/Cron/Tasks/MailerTask.php` → `Mailer::sendByRowQueue()` (also manual send in Settings → Mail).
- Dev/staging safety: `config/modules/Mail.php` → `MAIL_FILTER_SEND_ONLY_TO_DOMAIN`. Only listed `@domain` recipients get SMTP; others stripped; rows with no match drained without send. Off: `''` or `[]`. One: `'itconnect.pl'`. Several: `['a.pl', 'b.com']` or comma-separated string. Subdomains match. Not applied to `Mailer::test()` or OSSMail compose.
